GNATHOSOMA (
Fig. 2H, I
). Cheliceral blade with tricuspid cap; gnathobase with sparse puncta and 1 pair of branched gnathocoxal (tritorostral) setae; proximal part of cheliceral base and palpal femur with sparse puncta; galeal (deutorostral) seta branched; palpal claw with 3 prongs; setae on palpal femur and genu nude; dorsal palpal tibial seta branched, lateral and ventral palpal tibial setae nude; palpal tarsus with 7 branched setae and tarsala (
ω
).

